BIO

I am a Full Stack Web Developer based out of Denver, CO. I am currently working on a mobile app called Spinnr, it is a React Native project that I am building with another devoloper.

Spinnr.

React Native

Spinnr is a mobile app built using React Native. The app allows a user to take a photo of a record cover and have it automatically play in Spotify. Currently we are getting close to marketing our product before we launch our kickstarter. You can learn more at www.spinnrapp.com

General Assembly

Student

In 2017 I attended a 3 month coding boot camp at General Assembly. I studied Javascript and frameworks like Angular and React. I also built web apps using Node.js, Mongo Databases and Firebase. Since graduating I have kept busy improving my skills and learning new ones. I plan on continuing my education by learning php and python in the near future
